      • getDestination

        public java.net.URL getDestination(java.lang.Object request,
                                   java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> headers)
        Description copied from interface: RequestRoutingStrategy
        Returns the rerouted destination URL, or null if request is not to be rerouted. For HTTP protocol, this can be simply http://: if the request path should be the same on the target server. Or a full destination URL can be returned.
